00:00:10,625 --> 00:00:15,000
So, Megum-yan, just what do you
think you've done here?

4
00:00:15,083 --> 00:00:16,333
What's going on here?

5
00:00:16,416 --> 00:00:20,708
The judges are reacting
to Megumi Tadokoro's dish again.

6
00:00:20,791 --> 00:00:22,625
I get it. So that's the core
of the dorayaki.

7
00:00:22,708 --> 00:00:26,166
An apple confiture.

8
00:00:26,250 --> 00:00:29,166
It's a unique jam using
ginger to showcase the apples.

9
00:00:29,250 --> 00:00:31,916
When paired with the diced apple
and fluffy exterior,

10
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:35,500
the flavor profile
is most remarkable.

11
00:00:35,583 --> 00:00:39,750
It was Mr. Aldini who is ginger
for your dish, correct?

12
00:00:39,833 --> 00:00:42,291
Yes. I took some of
his shredded ginger

13
00:00:42,375 --> 00:00:44,291
and then I sliced up even finer
for what I needed.

14
00:00:44,375 --> 00:00:48,541
It hit me when I heard he'd be
using ginger for his dish.

15
00:00:48,625 --> 00:00:50,666
Following up the slightly sweet
bean paste

16
00:00:50,750 --> 00:00:51,958
with a filling like this

17
00:00:52,041 --> 00:00:54,125
would accentuate
the acid profile.

18
00:00:54,208 --> 00:00:57,125
It spreads across the tongue
and adds a sensational depth

19
00:00:57,208 --> 00:00:58,458
of flavor.

20
00:00:58,541 --> 00:01:00,333
The confiture and
apple infused butter --

21
00:01:00,416 --> 00:01:02,500
they seem like they're similar
ingredients,

22
00:01:02,583 --> 00:01:05,375
but it's the taste difference
between the two.

23
00:01:05,458 --> 00:01:08,041
In the end,
that's what makes my dorayaki.

24
00:01:08,125 --> 00:01:11,416
Whoo-hoo-hoo!
I can't belive you had that up
your sleeve this whole time!

25
00:01:11,500 --> 00:01:12,583
It's because they're color and
shape are similar.

26
00:01:12,666 --> 00:01:15,625
She was able
to deliver that perfect blow.

27
00:01:15,708 --> 00:01:17,666
That was a super bait
and switch.

28
00:01:17,750 --> 00:01:20,291
It's sure to count as a
powerful
parting shot for the judges.

29
00:01:20,375 --> 00:01:23,041
Urara: Okay, everyone, let's
check in with the judges

30
00:01:23,125 --> 00:01:24,458
to hear their decision.

31
00:01:24,541 --> 00:01:28,833
Anne: Sure enough, that was
a stealth punch of flavor.

32
00:01:28,916 --> 00:01:30,208
A finishing blow kept hidden

33
00:01:30,291 --> 00:01:32,208
from the opponent
right up 'til the end.

34
00:01:35,250 --> 00:01:37,000
I drive head on
into the enemy's vital area,

35
00:01:37,083 --> 00:01:39,500
and after I reach
their blind spot,

36
00:01:39,583 --> 00:01:41,208
I deliver!

37
00:01:42,583 --> 00:01:44,291
Uppercut!

