Hmm.
Whatever.

89
00:05:18,208 --> 00:05:20,291
Not cute.
Not cute. Not cute.

90
00:05:20,375 --> 00:05:23,833
Nope. Not cute at all,
Megumi Tadokoro.

91
00:05:23,916 --> 00:05:27,916
So not cute.

92
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:28,958
Are you really
not going to reach out

93
00:05:29,041 --> 00:05:32,708
to your young apprentice?

94
00:05:32,791 --> 00:05:35,083
She no longer needs a shoulder
to cry on.

95
00:05:35,166 --> 00:05:36,458
Instead, tell her this.

96
00:05:36,541 --> 00:05:40,250
If she really wants
to get better, she can come

97
00:05:40,333 --> 00:05:43,250
knock on the door of Shino's
Tokyo anytime she wants.

98
00:05:43,333 --> 00:05:49,708
♪♪

99
00:05:49,791 --> 00:05:53,583
Do your best out there!
I know you can do it!

100
00:05:53,666 --> 00:05:55,208
I get it, Megumi.

101
00:05:55,291 --> 00:05:57,458
There's no way you couldn't feel
beat up about this.

102
00:05:57,541 --> 00:06:00,000
Just you watch.
All of our teamwork

103
00:06:00,083 --> 00:06:01,333
won't have been
for nothing.

104
00:06:01,416 --> 00:06:05,041
Look. Takumi-poo started on
the beef, the theme
ingredient.

105
00:06:05,125 --> 00:06:08,125
He sliced it really thin and
then tossed it into sesame oil

106
00:06:08,208 --> 00:06:09,750
to let it
slowly build up the aroma.

107
00:06:09,833 --> 00:06:11,416
Once the fires
run its course,

108
00:06:11,500 --> 00:06:13,833
I'll throw in some ginger
and let it simmer.

109
00:06:13,916 --> 00:06:15,916
It looks like he might be making
a shigureni.

110
00:06:16,041 --> 00:06:17,458
Uniquely Japanese,

111
00:06:17,541 --> 00:06:19,333
it delights the tongue
by pairing sweetness

112
00:06:19,416 --> 00:06:21,375
with a bracing accent
of ginger.

113
00:06:21,458 --> 00:06:23,625
Name was inspired
by the intense flavors.

114
00:06:23,708 --> 00:06:24,916
They quickly come and go,

115
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:26,958
a lot like the Shigure
autumn showers.

116
00:06:27,041 --> 00:06:28,041
That's Takumi
for ya.

117
00:06:28,125 --> 00:06:29,750
He can do Japanese, too.

118
00:06:29,833 --> 00:06:32,041
What approach will he take
in bringing this dish?

119
00:06:32,125 --> 00:06:34,916
How will he elevate
the shigureni even further?

120
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:37,791
How have you solved
this riddle with brilliance?

121
00:06:40,041 --> 00:06:42,041
Whoa!
You're really good at that!

122
00:06:42,125 --> 00:06:42,958
You'll have to show me
your technique some time.

123
00:06:43,041 --> 00:06:44,333
Pizza dough's tough.

124
00:06:44,416 --> 00:06:46,666
Just focus on your own dish
right now, Soma.

125
00:06:46,750 --> 00:06:47,291
You hear me?

126
00:06:47,375 --> 00:06:48,625
Is that pizza dough?

127
00:06:48,708 --> 00:06:51,250
It looks like Takumi-poo plans
to make a pizza

128
00:06:51,333 --> 00:06:52,500
out of shigureni.

129
00:06:52,583 --> 00:06:55,125
Shigureni pizza?
How novel of him.

130
00:06:55,208 --> 00:06:58,416
Indeed. I look forward
to the finished product.

131
00:06:58,500 --> 00:07:00,750
Eizan: Well, well.
Shigureni, huh?

132
00:07:00,833 --> 00:07:05,125
[ Laughs ]

133
00:07:05,208 --> 00:07:06,833
You've risen above your loss
to Mimasaka

134
00:07:06,916 --> 00:07:09,041
at the fall selection
and managed to come this far,

135
00:07:09,125 --> 00:07:11,750
have you?
Splendid.

136
00:07:11,833 --> 00:07:16,166
You are indeed the very model
of a classic Italian chef.

137
00:07:16,250 --> 00:07:18,958
However, it would seem that,

138
00:07:19,041 --> 00:07:22,000
unfortunately, your pride
will be taking another beating,

139
00:07:22,083 --> 00:07:26,333
Takumi Aldini.

140
00:07:26,416 --> 00:07:27,583
Urara: And so,
here in the third bout,

141
00:07:27,666 --> 00:07:31,208
it's just the first
and second cards remaining.

142
00:07:31,291 --> 00:07:33,750
Everyone, watch how
Chef Eizan does it!

143
00:07:33,833 --> 00:07:35,291
Just look at
his incredibly thick meat.

144
00:07:35,375 --> 00:07:38,416
It's almost
criminally juicy.

145
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:41,375
That's a roasted beef
to steal the spotlight.

146
00:07:41,458 --> 00:07:44,083
There's more to it
than meets the eye.

147
00:07:44,166 --> 00:07:46,916
The flame has to penetrate
to the very center of the cut.

148
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:49,250
It's the most advanced
form of beef roasting.

149
00:07:49,333 --> 00:07:51,208
That's some
horseradish.

150
00:07:51,291 --> 00:07:54,750
But also there's fresh cream,
yogurt, and anchovies.

151
00:07:54,833 --> 00:07:56,750
It would seem he's making
a cream sauce

152
00:07:56,833 --> 00:07:58,541
to go with the roasted meat
he's prepared.

153
00:07:58,625 --> 00:08:01,000
There's no hesitation
to his movements.

154
00:08:01,083 --> 00:08:03,291
Sure enough, someone skilled
enough to be in the Ten

155
00:08:03,375 --> 00:08:04,958
has first rate
cooking skills.

156
00:08:05,041 --> 00:08:07,208
What the hell
are you praising him for?

157
00:08:07,291 --> 00:08:08,500
Have you forgotten
what that A-hole did

158
00:08:08,583 --> 00:08:10,250
to our beloved
Kyokuse?

159
00:08:10,333 --> 00:08:12,541
Of course not. There's no way
I can forget that.

160
00:08:15,333 --> 00:08:17,916
Do your best,
Takumi-kun!

161
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,416
Don't lose to
that smart-ass thug!

162
00:08:19,500 --> 00:08:22,500
Get that douche!
Crush that A-hole!

163
00:08:22,583 --> 00:08:25,625
They're all
counting on you.

164
00:08:25,708 --> 00:08:28,250
Although it was
for the revolution,

165
00:08:28,333 --> 00:08:31,000
I'll admit I did
a terrible thing to your dorm.

166
00:08:31,083 --> 00:08:34,250
The fact is, I seem to provoke
the ire of others,

167
00:08:34,333 --> 00:08:37,250
including you, I presume.
Yes?

168
00:08:37,333 --> 00:08:39,041
Still, it was
Mimasaka

169
00:08:39,125 --> 00:08:41,625
who challenged you to a food war
at the selection.

170
00:08:41,708 --> 00:08:43,375
I was merely overseeing
the proceedings,

171
00:08:43,458 --> 00:08:45,916
and in good faith
at that.

172
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:47,416
I would say it's a mistake
for you

173
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:49,750
to direct
your spite at me.

174
00:08:49,833 --> 00:08:51,083
Spite, huh?

175
00:08:51,166 --> 00:08:52,250
A single word
could not express

176
00:08:52,333 --> 00:08:54,041
the depth of my emotions.

177
00:08:54,125 --> 00:08:57,416
Suffice it to say, I hold
no feelings of spite for you.

178
00:08:57,500 --> 00:09:00,208
I will beat you.
That's all there is.

179
00:09:00,291 --> 00:09:04,458
Eizan has become quite skilled
at rattling his adversary.

180
00:09:04,541 --> 00:09:06,625
Takumi makes a show
of indifference,

181
00:09:06,708 --> 00:09:07,666
but counter to his words,

182
00:09:07,750 --> 00:09:10,833
he seems more
unsure than before.

183
00:09:10,916 --> 00:09:13,125
Heh.

184
00:09:13,208 --> 00:09:14,791
Takumi-poo
let his dough rest

185
00:09:14,875 --> 00:09:16,125
and now he's
rolling it out!

186
00:09:16,208 --> 00:09:18,125
Now the cooking
really starts.

187
00:09:18,208 --> 00:09:20,958
He's giving the dough
a thin coating of sauce.

188
00:09:21,041 --> 00:09:22,416
For his topping,

189
00:09:22,500 --> 00:09:24,666
he's going to use that slow
simmered beef shigureni.

190
00:09:24,750 --> 00:09:27,250
And white onions
and mozzarella cheese.

191
00:09:27,333 --> 00:09:29,791
He'll cook it at 475
for 12 minutes.

192
00:09:29,875 --> 00:09:32,125
Then all that's left
is to wait for the crust,

193
00:09:32,208 --> 00:09:33,666
letting it get golden brown.

194
00:09:33,750 --> 00:09:35,708
Into the oven
you go.

195
00:09:35,791 --> 00:09:37,958
[ Speaking foreign ]

196
00:09:38,041 --> 00:09:40,291
[ Chuckles ]

197
00:09:40,375 --> 00:09:43,458
Your pizza looks
quite refined, Aldini.

198
00:09:43,541 --> 00:09:45,500
Making
any flavor adjustments

199
00:09:45,583 --> 00:09:47,166
once it's been baked
would prove to be difficult.

200
00:09:47,250 --> 00:09:50,083
What exactly are you saying?

201
00:09:50,166 --> 00:09:54,500
That you're done for,
you fool.

202
00:09:54,583 --> 00:09:57,666
There is one more ingredient
that will go into my cream sauce

203
00:09:57,750 --> 00:09:59,458
before I'm finished.

204
00:09:59,541 --> 00:10:01,208
Artichokes.

205
00:10:01,291 --> 00:10:02,750
This unassuming vegetable
is known to have an abundance

206
00:10:02,833 --> 00:10:05,458
of the bitter compound
called cynarine.

207
00:10:05,541 --> 00:10:08,500
Its main characteristic is that
it inhibits

208
00:10:08,583 --> 00:10:10,500
the taste receptors
on the tongue

209
00:10:10,583 --> 00:10:12,541
and tricks the person
who is eating so much so

210
00:10:12,625 --> 00:10:14,083
that anything
eaten afterward

211
00:10:14,166 --> 00:10:16,583
is perceived as much sweeter
than intended.

212
00:10:16,666 --> 00:10:17,750
For real?
For real?
It can do that?!

213
00:10:17,833 --> 00:10:21,833
It's possible. For example,
serving a dessert

214
00:10:21,916 --> 00:10:24,416
immediately following
an artichoke dish will
intensify

215
00:10:24,500 --> 00:10:26,083
and add to the sweetness.

216
00:10:26,166 --> 00:10:29,000
A lot of famous chefs
make use of that knowledge.

217
00:10:29,083 --> 00:10:32,708
Your shigureni dish is one
of intensely rich sweetness.

218
00:10:32,791 --> 00:10:35,708
Should one eat artichoke prior,
what do you think will happen

219
00:10:35,791 --> 00:10:38,458
to that sweetness
that you so counted on?

220
00:10:38,541 --> 00:10:41,625
You have about ten minutes
before your pizza is done,

221
00:10:41,708 --> 00:10:43,958
meaning my dish
will be ready before yours.

222
00:10:44,041 --> 00:10:47,166
Taking into consideration
that you will be judged next,

223
00:10:47,250 --> 00:10:48,875
your dish will be
cloyingly sweet,

224
00:10:48,958 --> 00:10:52,958
and I expect considerably
less savory than you thought!

225
00:10:53,041 --> 00:10:54,708
What in the H?!

226
00:10:54,791 --> 00:10:57,000
That's one dirty trick to pull
at the last minute, buttwad!

227
00:10:57,083 --> 00:10:57,958
Don't you have
any damn pride?

228
00:10:58,041 --> 00:11:00,125
Hey, judges!
You need to disqualify

229
00:11:00,208 --> 00:11:02,166
this no-good punk and kick
his pathetic ass

230
00:11:02,250 --> 00:11:03,291
to the curb!

231
00:11:03,375 --> 00:11:05,041
But why would we?

232
00:11:05,125 --> 00:11:07,375
He merely learned
his opponent's intent,

233
00:11:07,458 --> 00:11:08,666
then devised a way
to counter it

234
00:11:08,750 --> 00:11:10,541
within
the prescribed time limits.

235
00:11:10,625 --> 00:11:11,916
He has done nothing wrong.

236
00:11:13,541 --> 00:11:15,291
No way.

237
00:11:15,375 --> 00:11:17,916
Eizan:
Now then, if you'll allow me
to complete my dish

238
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:23,125
with an insane amount of cut-up
artichoke!

239
00:11:23,208 --> 00:11:24,541
Takumi Aldini!

240
00:11:24,625 --> 00:11:27,083
You are indeed naive, boy!

241
00:11:27,166 --> 00:11:29,750
This time and the time before!

242
00:11:29,833 --> 00:11:32,541
And when your Mezzaluna
was taken from you as well,

243
00:11:32,625 --> 00:11:36,250
if it were that man
standing over there instead,

244
00:11:36,333 --> 00:11:39,458
if it were Soma Yukihira
rather than just you,

245
00:11:39,541 --> 00:11:40,833
I'm sure
he'd find a way!

246
00:11:44,416 --> 00:11:48,250
Here's my completed dish,
Roast Beef of Enchantment,

247
00:11:48,333 --> 00:11:49,791
the Etsuya Eizan
special edition.

248
00:11:55,375 --> 00:11:56,875
Ah! He just finished
his dish!

249
00:11:56,958 --> 00:11:59,416
Not only is it swimming in
and beefy juices...

250
00:11:59,500 --> 00:12:01,250
...he's paired it
with a runny poached egg.

251
00:12:01,333 --> 00:12:03,791
That dish is going to be way
too friggin' delish.

252
00:12:03,875 --> 00:12:04,791
So, does that mean
Takumi-poo's pizza

253
00:12:04,875 --> 00:12:06,916
would have been
all for nothing

254
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:09,083
because of that
cynarine crap?

255
00:12:09,166 --> 00:12:12,000
So very beautiful,
such vibrancy.

256
00:12:12,083 --> 00:12:13,791
It delights the tongue
in anticipation

257
00:12:13,875 --> 00:12:15,166
of the flavors to come.

258
00:12:17,541 --> 00:12:19,916
This deliciousness will go down
in history!

259
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:21,458
Wow. I've never had
a dish infused

260
00:12:21,541 --> 00:12:24,625
with so much
blatant artichoke.

261
00:12:24,708 --> 00:12:26,541
Yes, and yet, it makes you want
to eat more and more.

262
00:12:26,625 --> 00:12:29,625
Something won't
stop bugging me.

263
00:12:29,708 --> 00:12:32,875
How does that artichoke thing
he made on the sly taste?

264
00:12:32,958 --> 00:12:35,875
It's killing me.
I want to try some.

265
00:12:35,958 --> 00:12:37,333
So, that's what
was bothering you?

266
00:12:37,416 --> 00:12:41,541
Well, an inquisitive spirit
like that is to be applauded.

267
00:12:41,625 --> 00:12:43,458
Would the two of you
like to try it?

268
00:12:43,541 --> 00:12:45,958
Ah. Can I?
Wait. Me, too?

269
00:12:50,791 --> 00:12:53,166
The cream sauce
adds a tingling sensation

270
00:12:53,250 --> 00:12:55,875
that's the perfect cover for the
richness of the roast beef!

271
00:12:55,958 --> 00:12:58,583
And its juices pack an
incredible punch,

272
00:12:58,666 --> 00:13:00,500
but the vegetables'
unique bitterness

273
00:13:00,583 --> 00:13:03,000
and depth of flavor
are right up front!

274
00:13:03,083 --> 00:13:06,041
This, too, is the cynarine's
sneaky handywork.

275
00:13:06,125 --> 00:13:08,333
By eliminating
unnecessary sweetness,

276
00:13:08,416 --> 00:13:11,166
the cream sauce's flavor
becomes more refined.

277
00:13:11,250 --> 00:13:14,375
Cynarine can have a direct
effect on the taste receptors.

278
00:13:14,458 --> 00:13:17,208
Yes. Its components blanket
the areas of the tongue

279
00:13:17,291 --> 00:13:18,916
that experience
sweetness.

280
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:21,416
This is what the judges
are currently experiencing.

281
00:13:21,500 --> 00:13:24,958
With sweetness dulled, bitter
ones become that much sharper.

282
00:13:25,041 --> 00:13:26,416
Eat something else, and the
chewing will slowly

283
00:13:26,500 --> 00:13:28,125
clear away the cynarine.

284
00:13:28,208 --> 00:13:31,666
Your taste receptors will go
back to functioning normally,

285
00:13:31,750 --> 00:13:32,291
as they did
before you encountered

286
00:13:32,375 --> 00:13:34,958
such an effect.

287
00:13:35,041 --> 00:13:37,958
Now, with the sweet receptors
having been dulled thus far,

288
00:13:38,041 --> 00:13:39,583
even something slightly sweet
people certainly stand out.

289
00:13:39,666 --> 00:13:42,166
All:
Makes sense, I guess?

290
00:13:42,250 --> 00:13:44,041
They say with enough cynarine
remaining on the tongue,

291
00:13:44,125 --> 00:13:48,125
even simple water can seem
dangerously sweet in comparison.

292
00:13:48,208 --> 00:13:50,583
So, you're saying the sweetness
of Takumi's shigureni

293
00:13:50,666 --> 00:13:52,208
is going to get
ramped up as well?

294
00:13:52,291 --> 00:13:55,125
And by the time the judges
have finished eating his pizza,

295
00:13:55,208 --> 00:13:57,500
the cynarine will have
totally worn off

296
00:13:57,583 --> 00:13:59,833
and it won't have any effect on
the dishes to be judged later.

297
00:13:59,916 --> 00:14:02,708
Chef Eizan on knew
what would happen,

298
00:14:02,791 --> 00:14:04,791
and he used that
to his advantage.

299
00:14:04,875 --> 00:14:06,750
His knowledge actually
runs that deep?

300
00:14:06,833 --> 00:14:09,833
True enough, he's amassed
a wealth of culinary
knowledge.

301
00:14:09,916 --> 00:14:13,208
Ikumi:
So his nickname, the Alchemist,
is it just for show!

302
00:14:13,291 --> 00:14:14,916
[ All grunting ]

303
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:18,000
It's like a chemical conversion
in my mouth.

304
00:14:18,083 --> 00:14:19,458
A miracle of flavor.

305
00:14:19,541 --> 00:14:20,916
[ Swallows ]

306
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:23,500
This deliciousness
is like stage magic

307
00:14:23,583 --> 00:14:25,416
of the highest caliber,

308
00:14:25,500 --> 00:14:28,958
an inescapable illusion!

309
00:14:29,041 --> 00:14:30,416
[ Alarm beeping ]

310
00:14:30,500 --> 00:14:33,583
Ah! Takumi-poo's
pizza is done!

311
00:14:33,666 --> 00:14:35,916
Well, Aldini, that's quite
the long face.

312
00:14:36,041 --> 00:14:39,458
I know. Why not have
the judges drink some water

313
00:14:39,541 --> 00:14:40,958
before they eat?
It might actually help out

314
00:14:41,041 --> 00:14:42,833
with the effects
of the cynarine a little bit.

315
00:14:42,916 --> 00:14:46,000
All: Yeah! Have a little
sip or something!

316
00:14:46,083 --> 00:14:48,625
No, I'm fine
with it as is.

317
00:14:48,708 --> 00:14:51,291
Well, it's a good thing,
accepting one's fate.

318
00:14:51,375 --> 00:14:53,541
Don't have to,
because I will win.

319
00:14:53,625 --> 00:14:54,791
What?

320
00:14:56,708 --> 00:14:58,208
Takumi.

321
00:15:00,541 --> 00:15:01,958
The pizza.

322
00:15:02,041 --> 00:15:05,166
He should have made
the shigureni the main topping.

323
00:15:05,250 --> 00:15:06,958
Ah.

324
00:15:07,041 --> 00:15:10,458
The all-important shigureni
is only on half of it.

325
00:15:10,541 --> 00:15:12,625
Shoji: The other half
is cheese only?

326
00:15:12,708 --> 00:15:14,000
Daigo:
That's way too simple!

327
00:15:14,083 --> 00:15:15,375
Oh, no.

328
00:15:15,458 --> 00:15:17,625
What are Takumi's
chances of winning?

329
00:15:23,250 --> 00:15:24,625
Buon appetito.

330
00:15:24,708 --> 00:15:25,875
Huh.
So I see.

331
00:15:25,958 --> 00:15:28,375
The left
and right side toppings

332
00:15:28,458 --> 00:15:31,833
are clearly separated, much like
a Japanese delivery pizza.

333
00:15:31,916 --> 00:15:34,666
Is it acceptable
to eat this by hand?

334
00:15:34,750 --> 00:15:38,416
In Italy, it is common to use
a knife and fork to eat pizza.

335
00:15:38,500 --> 00:15:40,708
Please feel free to eat
it however you wish.

336
00:15:40,791 --> 00:15:43,166
How you decide to eat the pizza
won't affect

337
00:15:43,250 --> 00:15:43,916
how delicious it is.

338
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:46,291
However, there is one thing.

339
00:15:46,375 --> 00:15:48,833
I would ask you all
to heed the words of your chef,

340
00:15:48,916 --> 00:15:52,708
and that would be for you
to begin eating

341
00:15:52,791 --> 00:15:53,750
with the shigureni side
on the right.

342
00:15:53,833 --> 00:15:56,000
Hold on
just a minute!

343
00:15:56,083 --> 00:15:57,708
But the cynarine would make
all the sweetness

344
00:15:57,791 --> 00:15:59,041
count against it.

345
00:15:59,125 --> 00:16:01,875
What are you even thinking,
Takumi?

346
00:16:01,958 --> 00:16:03,916
Well then, I'll begin
with the shigureni.

347
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:06,041
I'm sure its taste
is sublime.

348
00:16:06,125 --> 00:16:08,500
Or yet, would
have been normally

349
00:16:08,583 --> 00:16:10,541
if it weren't for
the cynarine.

350
00:16:10,625 --> 00:16:14,250
Given the nature of this
contest, it can't be helped.

351
00:16:14,333 --> 00:16:16,458
[ All groan ]

352
00:16:17,708 --> 00:16:18,791
[ Gasps ]

353
00:16:18,875 --> 00:16:20,125
[ All gasp ]

354
00:16:20,208 --> 00:16:21,416
This deliciousness is simply
unrivaled!

355
00:16:21,500 --> 00:16:23,666
[ Groaning ]

356
00:16:23,750 --> 00:16:26,541
What the --
But how can that be?!

357
00:16:26,625 --> 00:16:29,083
I used a yuzu and miso
sauce on the pizza dough.

358
00:16:29,166 --> 00:16:32,000
It was a combination I'd already
decided upon.

359
00:16:32,083 --> 00:16:35,125
As intended, I took the miso,
sugar, and mirin,

360
00:16:35,208 --> 00:16:36,541
but scaled back
as much as possible

361
00:16:36,625 --> 00:16:39,666
to account for the chemical
components of the cynarine.

362
00:16:39,750 --> 00:16:42,000
And instead, I use yuzu juice
to bump up the acidity level,

363
00:16:42,083 --> 00:16:45,333
and I even added
some grated rind to it.

364
00:16:45,416 --> 00:16:47,000
That added bitterness
and sourness.

365
00:16:47,083 --> 00:16:50,166
I assumed that Chef Eizan's
roasted beef dish

366
00:16:50,250 --> 00:16:51,833
would be eaten first,

367
00:16:51,916 --> 00:16:54,666
so I had to adjust
the flavor balance.
[ Gasps ]

368
00:16:54,750 --> 00:16:56,166
The way this was put together
has made the shigureni

369
00:16:56,250 --> 00:16:59,541
much more flavorful
than if eaten on its own.

370
00:16:59,625 --> 00:17:02,916
A normal Italian menu
always starts with an
appetizer

371
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:04,583
so that the diner
can look forward

372
00:17:04,666 --> 00:17:06,541
to the upcoming main course,

373
00:17:06,625 --> 00:17:08,875
which, as you know,
is the secondo piatto

374
00:17:08,958 --> 00:17:11,625
Mr. Aldini's approach was to
make his rival's meal

375
00:17:11,708 --> 00:17:13,125
the appetizer,

376
00:17:13,208 --> 00:17:15,166
and his own dish the actual main
star of the show.

377
00:17:15,250 --> 00:17:18,416
Mr. Eizan's offering became
a little more

378
00:17:18,500 --> 00:17:20,916
than an opening act.

379
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:22,833
Impossible.
You bastard.

380
00:17:22,916 --> 00:17:25,208
Are you saying you already had
that sauce combination in mind?

381
00:17:25,291 --> 00:17:28,375
I only used artichokes
as a countermeasure

382
00:17:28,458 --> 00:17:29,958
after seeing
the shigureni!

383
00:17:30,041 --> 00:17:32,333
That way, you couldn't see
what I was really up to.

384
00:17:32,416 --> 00:17:35,666
How could you possibly know I'd
be using artichokes in my dish?

385
00:17:35,750 --> 00:17:37,416
I knew from the start.
What?

386
00:17:37,500 --> 00:17:39,333
I knew the instant that the
theme ingredient was announced

387
00:17:39,416 --> 00:17:44,500
that you would stoop low enough
and want to use artichokes.

388
00:17:44,583 --> 00:17:46,791
There were few ingredients
in the storehouse

389
00:17:46,875 --> 00:17:47,833
that could be used
to counteract sweetness.

390
00:17:47,916 --> 00:17:51,625
For example,
the miracle fruit,

391
00:17:51,708 --> 00:17:53,125
which is known to turn
sweetness into sourness.

392
00:17:53,208 --> 00:17:56,666
But the miraculin glycoprotein
it contains

393
00:17:56,750 --> 00:17:57,875
lasts about two hours,
give or take.

394
00:17:57,958 --> 00:18:00,625
This would affect subsequent
judgings

395
00:18:00,708 --> 00:18:02,166
for the rest of the day.

396
00:18:02,250 --> 00:18:05,791
Knowing all that, it only left
artichokes as an option.

397
00:18:05,875 --> 00:18:07,375
I've been watching you
this whole time,

398
00:18:07,458 --> 00:18:09,708
and so I followed
your twisted line of thinking.

399
00:18:09,791 --> 00:18:12,000
That led me
to the only remaining option

400
00:18:12,083 --> 00:18:15,333
I figured you would use,
just as I'd planned all along.

401
00:18:15,416 --> 00:18:17,250
Ah...
It can't be.

402
00:18:17,333 --> 00:18:19,916
That means he wasn't
just glaring at me

403
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:21,125
out of plain resentment.

404
00:18:21,208 --> 00:18:22,875
Since the third bout began,

405
00:18:22,958 --> 00:18:25,250
he's been watching me
this whole time.

406
00:18:25,333 --> 00:18:26,916
He's had me pegged
from the start.

407
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:29,333
Takumi:
Yes, that's right.

408
00:18:29,416 --> 00:18:32,166
You're still the same,
and your past 21 food wars,

409
00:18:32,250 --> 00:18:33,625
you've used
your opponent's strength

410
00:18:33,708 --> 00:18:35,375
against them 12 times.

411
00:18:35,458 --> 00:18:38,166
I was sure you used the same
approach this time as well.

412
00:18:38,250 --> 00:18:41,458
Go on, keep going
with your same sad approach,

413
00:18:41,541 --> 00:18:43,208
not knowing that I've seen
right through you.

414
00:18:43,291 --> 00:18:44,500
Yes.
Be the jerk you are.

415
00:18:44,583 --> 00:18:47,958
I'm sensing some real feelings
of resentment here.

416
00:18:48,041 --> 00:18:50,375
Yeah. Something about
Takumi-poo
is different this time
around.

417
00:18:50,458 --> 00:18:54,000
He's far more persistent
than he would appear to be.

418
00:18:54,083 --> 00:18:56,583
I can say the same thing
about you too.
Huh?

419
00:18:56,666 --> 00:19:00,875
It's kind of like something
Mimasaka would do.

420
00:19:00,958 --> 00:19:02,875
Who would have thought that
the cynarine's effect

421
00:19:02,958 --> 00:19:04,375
could be used against
itself?

422
00:19:04,458 --> 00:19:06,875
They used their mutual enmity
to outsmart each other,

423
00:19:06,958 --> 00:19:08,041
a battle of lesser
domain!

424
00:19:08,125 --> 00:19:12,125
The deliciousness
of this pizza is truly...

425
00:19:12,208 --> 00:19:16,625
Both:
...an inescapable illusion!

426
00:19:19,291 --> 00:19:20,500
Hell yeah!

427
00:19:20,583 --> 00:19:21,500
Desecrate Eizan,
dude!

428
00:19:21,583 --> 00:19:24,541
And yet, the menu I have
prepared for you

429
00:19:24,625 --> 00:19:25,083
is not yet finished.

430
00:19:25,166 --> 00:19:27,291
[ All gasp ]

431
00:19:27,375 --> 00:19:29,833
Italian cuisine generally
doesn't have a third course

432
00:19:29,916 --> 00:19:31,250
when dining
at a restaurant.

433
00:19:31,333 --> 00:19:34,125
But I wanted to break new ground
in today's bout,

434
00:19:34,208 --> 00:19:36,583
so the other half of this pizza
does just that

435
00:19:36,666 --> 00:19:37,958
with the cuisine
I've chosen.

436
00:19:38,041 --> 00:19:38,791
Terzo piatto.

437
00:19:38,875 --> 00:19:42,083
A third place.

438
00:19:42,166 --> 00:19:45,333
Well, fancy that. That pizza
he made looks just like

439
00:19:45,416 --> 00:19:47,583
two half moons.
[ Gasps ]
Half moons.

440
00:19:47,666 --> 00:19:48,833
A Mezzaluna!

441
00:19:48,916 --> 00:19:54,750
My dish is actually called
a double half moon pizza.

442
00:19:54,833 --> 00:19:57,833
Now you will experience
its true flavor.

443
00:19:58,666 --> 00:20:00,041
[ Grunts ]

444
00:20:00,125 --> 00:20:04,375
The other half is just cheese.
He's betting victory on that?

445
00:20:07,375 --> 00:20:07,708
[ Both gasp ]

446
00:20:07,791 --> 00:20:09,416
Oh, God!

447
00:20:09,500 --> 00:20:11,250
[ All gasp ]

448
00:20:11,333 --> 00:20:13,958
He has used for different types
of cheeses for this half.

449
00:20:14,041 --> 00:20:16,875
Mozzarella, parmesan,
gorgonzola, and ricotta.

450
00:20:16,958 --> 00:20:20,291
In other words,
we have a quattro formaggi!

451
00:20:20,375 --> 00:20:22,625
These normal toppings
in Italian cuisine.

452
00:20:22,708 --> 00:20:24,291
But combining them
is rare.

453
00:20:24,375 --> 00:20:26,208
It's a perfect match
for the crust,

454
00:20:26,291 --> 00:20:27,916
which was baked
a golden brown,

455
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:31,083
and has a hint of black pepper
to provide a spicy accent.

456
00:20:31,166 --> 00:20:34,125
The difference between this and
the sweetness of the shigureni

457
00:20:34,208 --> 00:20:36,833
lends such an amazing
depth of flavor.

458
00:20:36,916 --> 00:20:38,833
From the bitterness
of the artichokes

459
00:20:38,916 --> 00:20:40,375
to the sweetness of
the shigureni,

460
00:20:40,458 --> 00:20:43,458
then the saltiness of
the quattro formaggi.

461
00:20:43,541 --> 00:20:45,125
Uno.

462
00:20:45,208 --> 00:20:46,666
Due.

463
00:20:46,750 --> 00:20:48,666
Tre!

464
00:20:48,750 --> 00:20:53,000
It invites the diner to the far
reaches of heaven in...

465
00:20:53,083 --> 00:20:56,500
All: A triple jump
of deliciousness!

466
00:20:56,583 --> 00:20:59,208
That's how confident
I was that from my experience

467
00:20:59,291 --> 00:21:02,500
of baking more pizzas
than I can count,

468
00:21:02,583 --> 00:21:04,708
I knew I can make the
ultimate quattro formaggi,

469
00:21:04,791 --> 00:21:07,916
one that was a perfect match
for the shigureni.

470
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:10,666
But that's not all.
If not for the Stagiaire,

471
00:21:10,750 --> 00:21:13,125
the shigureni pizza
would not have been possible,

472
00:21:13,208 --> 00:21:15,208
and if not for
my battle with Mimasaka,

473
00:21:15,291 --> 00:21:16,583
it wouldn't have occurred to me

474
00:21:16,666 --> 00:21:18,916
to follow my opponent's
way of thinking.

475
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:21,666
All the losses, all the trials
I've endured up until now,

476
00:21:21,750 --> 00:21:25,583
the taste of those experiences
are what let me make this dish,

477
00:21:25,666 --> 00:21:26,791
and it's thanks to you for
having pitted me up

478
00:21:26,875 --> 00:21:29,500
against Mimasaka.

479
00:21:29,583 --> 00:21:34,291
It's what kept me moving forward
up to this very point.

480
00:21:34,375 --> 00:21:36,375
He saw right through
my intentions

481
00:21:36,458 --> 00:21:38,000
and used them to present
the judges

482
00:21:38,083 --> 00:21:40,541
with a dish
of high voltage deliciousness,

483
00:21:40,625 --> 00:21:43,958
just like Subaru Mimasaka
did to him prior.

484
00:21:44,041 --> 00:21:45,541
This time,
he had me dancing

485
00:21:45,625 --> 00:21:48,333
in the palm of his hand.

486
00:21:48,416 --> 00:21:49,875
Damn you,

487
00:21:49,958 --> 00:21:52,333
you friggin' annoying
first year!

488
00:21:52,416 --> 00:21:54,250
Urara: In the second code
of the third bout,

489
00:21:54,333 --> 00:21:57,791
the winner is
from the rebel's side,

490
00:21:57,875 --> 00:21:59,583
Takumi Aldini.

491
00:21:59,666 --> 00:22:01,833
♪♪

492
00:22:01,916 --> 00:22:04,541
Grazie!

493
00:22:05,125 --> 00:22:07,708
[ Singing in Japanese ]

494
00:22:07,791 --> 00:22:16,416
♪♪

